summary: An Ordinance accepting the relinquishment of the franchise for newspaper vending machines granted to Post Intelligencer Company by Ordinance No. 31661 entitled "An Ordinance granting to Post Intelligencer Company, a corporation, its successors and assigns, a franchise to locate, erect, maintain and operate on the public streets, avenues, alleys and places within the City of Seattle, coin actuated newspaper vending machine" approved on August 14, 1913 as amended.
